<!--
  WickedSalemWitchCityTour v1.5
  Copyright (c) 2026 Destructive AI Gurus, LLC. All rights reserved.

  S249/S250 — Debug-only manifest overlay.

  V1 retail (release/AAB) builds ship with INTERNET + ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE
  STRIPPED from the main manifest (per S180, see feedback_v1_no_external_contact.md
  + the comment block at app-salem/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml:20-23).
  The OS denies any net access at the syscall layer regardless of code.

  Debug builds need INTERNET re-added so the SuperAdmin runtime override
  (`com.example.locationmapapp.util.SuperAdminMode`) can actually reach the
  cache-proxy at http://10.0.0.229:4300 when the operator toggles it on
  via the toolbar button (`SalemMainActivitySuperAdmin.wireSuperAdminToolbar`).

  S250: also override <application android:networkSecurityConfig> to allow
  cleartext HTTP to LAN cache-proxy. Without this, Android API 28+ blocks
  plain HTTP and OkHttp throws UnknownServiceException ("CLEARTEXT
  communication to 10.0.0.229 not permitted by network security policy")
  before ever hitting the wire — found via Lenovo logcat S250-1.

  Manifest merge: release/AAB pulls only src/main/. Debug merges debug + main
  → INTERNET + ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE present + cleartext config present in
  debug APK only.
  Verify: `apkanalyzer manifest print app-salem-release.apk | grep INTERNET`
  must return zero hits AND no networkSecurityConfig attribute.
-->
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools">

    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE" />

    <application
        android:networkSecurityConfig="@xml/network_security_config"
        tools:replace="android:networkSecurityConfig" />

</manifest>
